definitions: Past participle of fly; to have moved through the air using wings or an engine.
Past participle of fly; to have traveled by aircraft.
Past participle of fly; to have moved or passed swiftly.
Past participle of fly; to have displayed or waved in the air.
examples: The birds have flown south for the winter.
She had flown to Paris many times.
Time has flown by since we last met.
The flag has flown proudly over the building.
